    Verse: 6
Tags:
  - Doubt
---
Doubt is the disease of this inquisitive, restless age. It is the price
we pay for our advanced intelligence and civilization -- the dim light of
our resplendent day. But as the most beautiful night is born of darkness,
so the faith that springs from conflict is often the strongest and best.
